<item>
            <title>[DERBY-4427] TestConfiguration.existingServerSuite(....,portNumber) must use the supplied portNumber</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-4427</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When testing distributed replication I found that test clients/load would always use (default) port 1527 even if a different master port number had been specified. The correct/specified port number was used when starting the master server. &lt;br/&gt;
This was caused by a call to &apos;TestConfiguration.getCurrent().getPort()&apos; on an uninitialized TestConfiguration. The fix is to use the supplied portNumber parameter.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
